The article is a statement by the National Security Council Spokesperson, Bernadette Meehan, regarding American journalist Austin Tice. Tice has been in captivity for 1,000 days after being abducted in August 2012 while reporting from a suburb of Damascus in Syria. The US government is committed to bringing Tice back home to his family and appreciates the efforts of the Czech government, acting as the US protecting power in Syria. They urge Tice's captors to release him and ask anyone with information about his whereabouts to cooperate in bringing him home.